                        <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <i>Maryland Topography Viewer</i>
                                <p>
                                    The Maryland Topography Viewer is a web mapping application that allows users to 
                                    view and interact with the elevation services hosted 
                                    on the Maryland LiDAR Server. Users can view, query, print, and more on desktop and mobile devices.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <a target="_blank" href="@topoViewer"><i>Explore The Maryland Topography Viewer here</i></a>
                                </p>
                                <i>ArcGIS Online</i>
                                <p>
                                    To view Lidar in ArcGIS online, select any of the image thumbnails above under 
                                    Statewide or Countywide Services or search for Lidar on the Maryland State 
                                    ArcGIS online gallery at 
                                    <a target="_blank" href="http://maryland.maps.arcgis.com/home/index.html ">http://maryland.maps.arcgis.com/home/index.html
                                    </a>
                                </p>
                                <i>ArcGIS Desktop</i>
                                @*<span>To view in ArcDesktop/Catalog:</span>*@
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Launch ArcMap.</li>
                                    <li>Navigate to the ArcCatalog tab.</li>
                                    <li>In the ArcCatalog window expand GIS Servers.</li>
                                    <li>Select Add ArcGIS Server.</li>
                                    <li>Select Use GIS Services and click Next.</li>
                                    <li>The Server URL is: http://lidar.salisbury.edu/arcgis</li>
                                    <li>Click Finish (an alert may pop up notifying that the connection was made successfully).</li>
                                    <li>
                                        The new server connection will appear in the ArcCatalog window. After expanding the server, select the
                                        desired Image Service.
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                                <strong><small>* Viewing Tip</small></strong><br />
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        ArcGIS Desktop enables the use of raster functions. 
                                        Functions provide users with fast on-the-fly processing options without changing the actual data.
                                        Raster functions have been added to all of the countywide dem_m image services.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <span>To apply:</span>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Add in the countywide dem_m service</li>
                                            <li>Right click the service in the table of contents > Properties > Server Functions</li>
                                            <li>Select the Functions drop-down</li>
                                            <li>
                                                Choose one from the following function: Aspect, DEM_FT, Hillshade, None, Slope, Stretched. > Apply >
                                                Ok.
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                If choosing DEM_FT, an additional step is necessary.
                                                <br />
                                                <ul>
                                                    <li>Select Symbology > Scroll down to Statistics > Select From Current Display > Apply > Ok.</li>
                                                </ul>
                                            </li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <i>QGIS</i>
                                @*<span>To view in Quantum GIS</span>*@
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Select Layer > Add WMS Layer > Select New.</li>
                                    <li>Name the connection.</li>
                                    <li>
                                        Navigate to the service WMS page from the REST services directory and copy/paste the link into the URL
                                        field.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>*These services do not require a username and password.</li>
                                    <li>Select Ok.</li>
                                    <li>Select the service in the list of layers > Select Add > Close.</li>
                                </ol>
                                <i>Google Earth</i>
                                @*<span>To view in Google Earth:</span>*@
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Select the image service URL to open the service REST page</li>
                                    <li>On the REST page, select  View In: Google Earth</li>
                                    <li>This will prompt the download of a kmz file</li>
                                    <li>Open Google Earth and select File > Open</li>
                                    <li>Navigate to the download directory, select the downloaded service and select Open</li>
                                    <li>Double click the service once it appears under the “Places” tab to zoom to the service extent.</li>
                                </ol>
                                <i>AutoCAD</i>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Start AutoCAD</li>
                                    <li>Click the Add Image Server Connection  on the Image Server toolbar.</li>
                                    <li>The Add Image Server Connection dialog box is displayed.</li>
                                    <li>
                                        In the Server Name text box, type the name of the Lidar server:  http://lidar.salisbury.edu/arcgis.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>Double -click the Elevation folder to view the contained services.</li>
                                    <li>
                                        Double-click the image service in the list, or click the image service and click Select to
                                        to add the image service to the Selected Services list.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        The Service Properties dialog box is displayed. This dialog box shows the image service metadata and
                                        properties that you can view before opening the image service.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Click OK to close the Add Image Server Connection dialog box.                                        
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                                <p>
                                    <small>Instructions provided by ESRI resources:
                                        <a target="_blank" href="http://resources.esri.com/help/9.3/ArcGISImageServer/AutoCAD/HTML/index.htm#adding_an_image_service_in_autocad.htm">
                                            http://resources.esri.com/help/9.3/ArcGISImageServer/AutoCAD/HTML/index.htm#adding_an_image_service_in_autocad.htm
                                        </a>
                                    </small>
                                </p>
                                <i>Microstation</i>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Start MicroStation.</li>
                                    <li>Click the Add Server Connection button  in the MicroStation Image Server Client dialog box.</li>
                                    <li>The Add Image Server Connection dialog box is displayed.</li>
                                    <li>
                                        In the Server Name text box, type the name of the Lidar server:  http://lidar.salisbury.edu/arcgis.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>Double -click the Elevation folder to view the contained services.</li>
                                    <li>
                                        Double-click the image service in the list, or click the image service and click Select to add the image
                                        service to the Selected Services list.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        The Service Properties dialog box is displayed. This dialog box shows the image service metadata and
                                        properties that you can view before opening the image service.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>Click OK to close the Add Image Server Connection dialog box.</li>
                                </ol>
                                <p>
                                    <small>Instructions provided by ESRI resources:
                                        <a target="_blank" href="http://resources.esri.com/help/9.3/ArcGISImageServer/AutoCAD/HTML/index.htm#adding_an_image_service_in_autocad.htm">
                                            http://resources.esri.com/help/9.3/ArcGISImageServer/AutoCAD/HTML/index.htm#adding_an_image_service_in_autocad.htm
                                        </a>
                                    </small>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
