                                <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFive">How to extract the data for use
                                    in desktop processing</a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseFive" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>There are several methods to extract LIDAR data for use in desktop processing.</p>
                                <span>To extract based on a feature defined boundary:</span>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Load the service and feature mask into ArcMap</li>
                                    <li>In ArcToolbox, select the Extract by Mask tool under Spatial Analyst toolbox</li>
                                    <li>Select the image service as the input raster and the boundary feature class as the feature mask</li>
                                    <li>
                                        Specify the output raster name and directory location where the image will be saved and select OK.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>The image will be added to the map after processing.</li>
                                </ol>
                                <span>If you do not have the Spatial Analyst extension use the Export by data frame extent.</span>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Load the service into ArcMap</li>
                                    <li>Zoom to the AOI</li>
                                    <li>Right-click the service in the TOC and select Data > Export.</li>
                                    <li>From the Export dialog specify preferences and select Save.</li>
                                    <li>The image will be added to the map after processing.</li>
                                </ol>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
